dcterms:creator: The Library of Congress Classification
dcterms:description: A widely adopted and constantly updated taxonomy of all knowledge, including the category WORLD HISTORY and its direct subcategories.
dcterms:title: Library of Congress Classification

dcterms:creator: The Open Directory Project
dcterms:description: A taxonomy of web pages optimized for navigability rather than informativeness, featuring a hierarchical structure of labels.
dcterms:title: The Open Directory Project

dcterms:creator: The Gene Ontology Consortium
dcterms:description: A comprehensive ontology for the representation of gene function and its interaction with the genome, providing a structured framework for biological data.
dcterms:title: Gene Ontology

dcterms:creator: The LCC Ontology of Book Topics
dcterms:description: A taxonomy of book topics that organizes knowledge into a hierarchical structure for classification and retrieval purposes.
dcterms:title: LCC Ontology of Book Topics
